The paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms related to voting rules, which are typically studied in the field of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also introduces new distance measures and explores their relations with existing notions, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses strategic behavior in voting, which is a topic studied in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
